    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - LIGHT SYSTEMS - Luggage Box Lights
        - FAULT DETECTION MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="x08290209bb" svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION MANAGEMENT</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The testing method for troubleshooting the electrical systems portrayed in this manual is a basic
                    voltage test. An alternative method of checking for voltage drops within a given circuit may be a
                    quicker method of identifying an exact problem.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f082901188">Luggage Box Lights Circuits</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <para>A fault in the luggage box lights circuits will be apparent when the lights do not come on.</para>
        <figure id="f082901188" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg08/g082901188.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="496px"
                     scalefitheight="574px"/>
            <caption>Luggage Box Lights Circuits - Always Refer To Circuit Diagram Book For Latest Circuit Information
            </caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>CPC3 DASH AND TOE HARNESS TO SEALED ENGINE HARNESS</callout1>
                <callout1>J140 FLASHER PLATE TO DASH AND TOE</callout1>
                <callout1>SS8 SS20 SS21 SS22 SS23 SS24 SS25 SS204 SEALED ENGINE HARNESS TO LUGGAGE BOX LIGHTS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <table id="t08290209bb" tblwidth="pg-wide" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Luggage Box Lights Circuit Tests</title>
            <tgroup cols="6">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.67in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.68in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="0.63in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.89in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.87in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="1.90in"/>
                <spanspec namest="3" nameend="6" spanname="SPAN2"/>
                <spanspec namest="4" nameend="6" spanname="S4T6"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="S1T6"/>
                <spanspec namest="2" nameend="3" spanname="S2T3"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Luggage Box Lights Switch (C38) Voltage Checks</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>Check with ignition on, luggage box lights off and luggage box lights switch connector
                                (C38) disconnected.
                            </para>
                            <note>
                                <para>Always check connectors for damage and pushed-out terminals.</para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3" align="center">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Luggage box lights switch (C38) cavity 2 to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3" align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                            <para>If voltage is missing check for blown fuse #29 and check for short or open in circuit
                                16 BLK 35.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Luggage box lights switch (C38) cavity 2 to 3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3" align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                            <para>If voltage is missing check for short or open in circuit 16 BRN 35.</para>
                            <para>If circuits check good and lights are still faulty, replace luggage box lights
                                switch.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
